FBIS4-29447 "dreas118_h_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Thai Fishermen Arrested Near Redang Island Thai Fishermen Arrested Near Redang Island BK1706131094 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 GMT 17 Jun 94 BK1706131094 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia English BFN [Text] The Marine Division of the Fisheries Department has arrested 27 Thai fishermen in four trawlers for encroaching into Malaysia's exclusive economic zone. An official from the Terengganu State Fisheries Department said eight Thai fishing boats had been detained by the department so far this month. In yesterday's operation, the department's patrol boats were [word indistinct] spotted 10 foreign fishing boats near Pulau Redang [Redang Island] in the morning. He told newsmen four boats were detained, while the rest escaped. He said the detained fishermen between the ages of 15 to 51 years from Songkhla and Pak Phanang in Southern Thailand were being held at the police station.
